    "actor_description": "Something in me stops reaching. The future doesn't look bad so much as… blank-like a hallway with the lights out. My thoughts slow, heavy and unspecific. Even my breathing feels distant, like I'm listening to it from another room. I could speak, probably. I just can't find a reason that feels real.",
    "description_text": "{actor} goes still in a way that isn't restful. Their face flattens; their gaze loses its hook on the room. Movements come late and small, as if every gesture has to be hauled up from deep water.",
